The paper deals with an algorithmic problem in computational geometry, specifically the online Unit Covering problem in higher dimensions. This suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of competitive ratios of algorithms, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of Euclidean distance and $L_{2}$ norm suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper includes lower bounds on the competitive ratio, which is a topic in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
